content:
To improve a contact center’s call handling, supervisors can listen in to any ongoing call from Omni Supervisor. They can listen to only one call at a time. When a supervisor listens in to the call, the agent is notified in the chat transcript, but the customer isn’t.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
Contact Center Agent (Partner Telephony) OR Contact Center Agent AND 
Contact Center Supervisor AND 
Contact Center Admin

This feature is available with these telephony models: 
SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH AMAZON CONNECT SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY FROM AMAZON CONNECT SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY

A contact center supervisor must have view access to all instances of the Voice Call record before they can listen in to voice calls.

To let contact center supervisors listen in to voice calls, configure their security profile in Amazon Connect. 
From Amazon Connect, go to Manage users, and then Security profiles.
Assign this security profile the permissions to monitor live conversations.
Open Omni Supervisor.
From the Agents tab, expand a call, and click Monitor.
Only one of these options is shown at a time, depending on whether Multi-Party Calls and Enhanced Monitoring are enabled in Amazon Connect.
title: Supervisor Voice Call Monitoring
